Three men alleged to have plotted a coup against  the government of ex-president Kamuzu Banda have been released on bail, local  newspapers reported Monday.
Adaki Sulaimana, 26, retired army major McDonald Kunje and retired army  sergeant Finwell Mkwanda, who were arrested over Easter, were granted 10,000  kwacha (1,388 US dollars) bail.
They have pleaded not guilty to charges of conspiring with members of the  army to overthrow the government, inciting mutiny in the army and publishing  information with intent to cause public alarm.
The trial is due to start June 2.
Banda was beaten in presidential elections May 17 by Bakili Muluzi.
